# ── intentionally tracked despite gitignore patterns (PIN-1 + active docs) ─
# audit/ is a dir-level ignore: descent requires un-ignoring the dir, then
# re-ignoring its contents so only the pinned file is exposed (minimal set).
!/audit/
/audit/*
!/audit/structural/
/audit/structural/*
!audit/structural/compound_turn_pipeline_audit.md
!docs/07_PHASE4_SPRINT_LOG.md
# reports/** ignores subdirectories themselves — dir negations enable descent;
# contents stay matched by reports/** except the pinned files below.
!reports/audit_2026-04-30/
!reports/audit_2026-04-30/W1D_q49_dirichlet_rotation.md
!reports/investigations/
!reports/investigations/dexploit_handoff_20260606.md
!reports/investigations/exploit_probe_20260606.md
!reports/investigations/exploit_probe_design_20260606.md
!reports/investigations/finishing_discriminator_20260606.md
!reports/phase_b/
!reports/phase_b/v7full_selfplay/
!reports/phase_b/v7full_selfplay/baseline.md
!reports/s176_phase_b_prompt.md

# ── D-REPOCLEAN P3: docs/archive/ holds archived closed-sprint docs and IS
#    tracked. Negations placed last so they also beat the unanchored archive/
#    and audit/ dir rules and the *.jsonl rule for archived artifacts.
!docs/archive/
!docs/archive/**
